Why do you judge someone based on their religion?
If he were a Hindu, many Indians would be praising him. But since he’s a Muslim, suddenly there’s a problem. Seriously? This mindset is one of the reasons India is falling behind while other nations are moving forward—especially in terms of unity and economy.
Religion is just an identity. But no matter their religion, every person born in India is Indian. Respect should be given based on character and contribution—not based on whether someone is Hindu or Muslim.
And let’s not forget: the Muslims who stayed in India during Partition chose not to leave their motherland. That takes loyalty and courage. Disrespecting them or calling them slurs is not only wrong—it’s shameful.
